'''Leah Battle (formerly Mangue)''' is an illustrator who has created licensed artwork for [[Lucasfilm]]. She is the founder of the [[Nerf-Herders-Anonymous]] fansite.

In December [[2005]], her [[Star Wars Blog]] became a featured blog on [[StarWars.com]]. Her illustration of [[Boga/Legends|Boga]] the veractyl appeared in the ''[[Bantha Tracks (newsletter)|Bantha Tracks]]'' section of [[Star Wars Insider 90|''Star Wars Insider'' 90]]. Her Star Wars 30th Anniversary tribute artwork appeared in the ''[[Bantha Tracks (newsletter)|Bantha Tracks]]'' section of [[Star Wars Insider 97|''Star Wars Insider'' 97]]. She was chosen as an artist for ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[Celebration V]] with her print "Have Rifle Will Travel."

In [[May]] [[2007]], she was one of the sketch card artists for the ''[[2007 Topps Star Wars 30th Anniversary]]'' collectors card set. She has since worked on other [[The Topps Company, Inc.|Topps]] collectors card sets, including ''[[2008 Topps Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'', ''[[2009 Topps Star Wars: The Clone Wars Widevision]]'', ''[[2009 Topps Star Wars Galaxy Series 4]]'', ''[[2010 Topps Star Wars Galaxy Series 5]]'', ''[[2011 Topps Star Wars Galaxy Series 6]]'', ''[[2012 Topps Star Wars Galaxy Series 7]]'', and ''[[2012 Topps Star Wars Galactic Files Series 1]]''.

[[Joe Corroney]]'s illustration of [[Guri]] in ''[[Underworld: A Galaxy of Scum and Villainy]]'' was based on her appearance.<ref name="Hyperspace">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/89/indexp2.html|text=<nowiki>[N/A]</nowiki>|nobackup=1}}</ref>

